Problem Classification correctly:
A. Graph (dependencies / relationships / ordering)
B. DP (overlapping subproblems + optimal substructure)
C. Greedy (local choice is safe)
D. BFS/DFS state search (transformations / steps)
E. Math / bit / counting (representation matters more than process) / Greedy with constraint compression
F. Simulation (no optimization needed, just follow rules)   
   
Compression Thinking:
- Can I ignore order?
- Can I ignore positions?
- Can I reduce to counts?
- Can I reduce to graph?
- Can I reduce to state transitions?   
   
Separate these three steps:
- representation (what is the state?)
- Operation / process (what happens each step?)
- objective (what are we optimizing?)